      "message": "The value 2 does not limit the number of PAM modules. It represents the current number of user categories supported by OpenBMC:\n\nInternal (local) users → authenticated by pam_unix.so\nExternal (LDAP) users → authenticated by pam_ldap.so\n\nAdditional PAM modules such as pam_google_authenticator.so, pam_faillock.so, etc., are secondary authentication steps and do not define separate user types. \nThey apply on top of the primary UNIX/LDAP authentication but do not authenticate users independently.\n\nIf OpenBMC introduces a third authentication source (e.g., RADIUS, Kerberos), this constant can be updated. \n\nFor now, OpenBMC only has two actual user types, so defined maxPamModuleCount \u003d 2.",
